. This tournament is kind of like the playoffs for the laffs. Non existent and no players involved.  Wrong again Matthew!!! There are 8 Leafs playing in the tourney!!!  http://mapleleafs.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=892264

Oh well, I tried lol Ok. No players for Canada. The rest don't count  And Babcock is still a wing in my mind. His career is now over that he has tainted an otherwise brilliant career by getting that dreaded blue and white disease on his hands. Nice to Milan Michalek playing. Always liked that guy.

I wasn't sure about this going in, but after watching a few of the pre-tournament games I'll be probably watching very closely.  Team NA looks like they could skate circles around anyone, but I haven't watched them play a team that wasn't the orphaned Europeans team. Some of those guys look out of place and their defence is very suspect/immobile. I also think that if there's one team that doesn't have their hearts in it it would be the Euro team.

they dont need speed and talent, babcock is relying on his team being defensively unbeatable. The scorers will score he doesnt need to worry about that...until this injury there was a toews stamkos seguin line...you dont think they can score?
